00:18:29.110 --> 00:18:30.640
So they're sort of intermediate.

00:18:30.640 --> 00:18:33.640
And then your strong field
ligands-- with your strongest

00:18:33.640 --> 00:18:34.900
being cyanide.

00:18:34.900 --> 00:18:37.020
Very strong field ligand.

00:18:37.020 --> 00:18:41.890
All right, so, if your
metal has a weak field,

00:18:41.890 --> 00:18:44.380
intermediate field, or
strong field ligand,

00:18:44.380 --> 00:18:46.030
it can have very
different properties.

00:18:46.030 --> 00:18:48.190
Especially very
different colors.

00:18:48.190 --> 00:18:51.310
Also, it could be
paramagnetic or diamagnetic,

00:18:51.310 --> 00:18:53.680
depending on this.

