00:20:58.790 --> 00:21:01.680
splitting diagrams
and place electrons.

00:21:01.680 --> 00:21:08.720
And I already have, over here,
a starting place for those.

00:21:08.720 --> 00:21:13.160
So we're doing
here our d5 system.

00:21:13.160 --> 00:21:17.720
And we have a diagram
with a small splitting

00:21:17.720 --> 00:21:20.340
and one with a large splitting.

00:21:20.340 --> 00:21:22.260
So with the small
splitting, is that

00:21:22.260 --> 00:21:25.617
going to be a weak
field or a strong field?

00:21:25.617 --> 00:21:26.700
That will be a weak field.

00:21:29.240 --> 00:21:32.990
And when we have
a large splitting,

00:21:32.990 --> 00:21:37.120
that is a strong field

00:21:37.120 --> 00:21:41.030
OK, so which of
our two compounds

00:21:41.030 --> 00:21:43.860
is going to be the
