There, we have cyanide.

00:22:20.450 --> 00:22:24.050
So a weak, or intermediate
field, versus a strong field.

00:22:24.050 --> 00:22:27.572
All right, now we need
to put electrons in here.

00:22:27.572 --> 00:22:28.405
So I have to decide.

00:22:28.405 --> 00:22:31.050
I have five electrons
I'm going to play with.

00:22:31.050 --> 00:22:33.600
And I could put them in here.

00:22:33.600 --> 00:22:34.600
Let's just start here.

00:22:34.600 --> 00:22:36.570
Do one, two, three.

00:22:36.570 --> 00:22:39.630
Now the question is, where
am I going to put four?

00:22:39.630 --> 00:22:42.330
Am I going to put
four down here?

00:22:42.330 --> 00:22:44.180
Or put it up here?

00:22:44.180 --> 00:22:50.480
And so, here, it depends on, if
I put it down here on pairing--

00:22:50.480 --> 00:22:52.926
and, you know, the seats
on the bus-- people

00:22:52.926 --> 00:22:54.300
don't really want
to sit together

00:22:54.300 --> 00:22:55.341
if there are empty seats.

00:22:55.341 --> 00:22:58.110
Now there are empty
seats up here.

00:22:58.110 --> 00:23:03.020
So, the question is, is it going
to take more energy to pair?

00:23:03.020 --> 00:23:05.030
Or more energy to
put it up here?

00:23:05.030 --> 00:23:09.530
Now, if this is a weak
field, which it is,

00:23:09.530 --> 00:23:11.940
then that's not
all that far away.

00:23:11.940 --> 00:23:13.940
You get on a bus and you
see a seat in the back.

00:23:13.940 --> 00:23:15.481
You'd rather sit up
front, but you're

00:23:15.481 --> 00:23:18.230
like, than you have to sit with
someone, so you go to the back.

00:23:18.230 --> 00:23:20.660
So that's what happens
with a weak field.

00:23:20.660 --> 00:23:24.240
The other energy levels
are just not that far away,

00:23:24.240 --> 00:23:26.300
so you go up there.

00:23:26.300 --> 00:23:30.270
And if I kind of put
this up-- move it up

00:23:30.270 --> 00:23:34.590
for just a second-- and then
I'll say, so this rule here,

00:23:34.590 --> 00:23:36.870
and I'm going to kind
of cover this up again.

00:23:36.870 --> 00:23:38.820
But maybe I'll just
put it down here.

00:23:38.820 --> 00:23:39.920
This is in your notes.

00:23:39.920 --> 00:23:44.340
So here, the octahedral
crystal field splitting energy

00:23:44.340 --> 00:23:50.588
is less than we call PE,
which is pairing energy.

00:23:53.900 --> 00:23:57.910
So, it's not that far away.

00:23:57.910 --> 00:24:00.230
Just put them singly,
to the full extent

00:24:00.230 --> 00:24:04.590
possible, before you pair.

00:24:04.590 --> 00:24:07.550
So that's what happens
with a weak field.

00:24:07.550 --> 00:24:10.110
And we also can think
about how we're putting

00:24:10.110 --> 00:24:11.900
in our electrons parallel.

00:24:11.900 --> 00:24:15.410
We're not putting them in all
sorts of different directions.

00:24:15.410 --> 00:24:18.037
And we're not-- if we do pair--
