we're going to pair.

00:24:18.870 --> 00:24:20.390
So one's up, one's down.

00:24:20.390 --> 00:24:22.400
So all the rules that
we learned earlier

00:24:22.400 --> 00:24:23.400
are going to apply here.

00:24:23.400 --> 00:24:25.650
So this is good, good review.

00:24:25.650 --> 00:24:32.734
So now, in this case, we can put
in our first three electrons.

00:24:32.734 --> 00:24:33.650
And what do you think?

00:24:33.650 --> 00:24:35.180
Do you think I'm going to pair?

00:24:35.180 --> 00:24:40.160
Or do you think I'm
going to go up there?

00:24:40.160 --> 00:24:41.580
What do you think?

00:24:41.580 --> 00:24:42.270
I'm going pair.

00:24:42.270 --> 00:24:44.300
Yeah, I'm definitely
going to pair.

00:24:44.300 --> 00:24:46.960
So I'm going to put my
other two over here.

00:24:46.960 --> 00:24:51.500
So in this case, the pair--
the octahedral crystal field

00:24:51.500 --> 00:24:53.130
splitting energy--
it's so much fun

00:24:53.130 --> 00:24:55.430
to say that so many
times-- is greater

00:24:55.430 --> 00:24:57.270
than the pairing energy.

00:24:57.270 --> 00:24:59.850
And, so, in this case,
there might be empty seats.

00:24:59.850 --> 00:25:01.630
But maybe it's a long train.

00:25:01.630 --> 00:25:05.580
And there is-- you can sit
in car one with someone else,

00:25:05.580 --> 00:25:07.050
or carry all your luggage.

00:25:07.050 --> 00:25:08.390
Why did you bring so much?

