00:25:13.590 --> 00:25:15.460
You're just not going to do it.

00:25:15.460 --> 00:25:17.300
You don't have enough energy.

00:25:17.300 --> 00:25:20.210
You'd rather sit with
somebody up front.

00:25:20.210 --> 00:25:23.010
So how you put in
electrons depends if it's

00:25:23.010 --> 00:25:24.600
a weak field or strong field.

00:25:24.600 --> 00:25:29.510
It depends on whether it takes
just a little bit of energy,

00:25:29.510 --> 00:25:30.980
and it's worse to pair.

00:25:30.980 --> 00:25:32.850
Or takes a huge
amount of energy.

00:25:32.850 --> 00:25:35.630
There's a big splitting,
a really strong field.

00:25:35.630 --> 00:25:37.940
And in that case, you're
going to pair first.

00:25:37.940 --> 00:25:40.590
And you're only going to
put electrons up here when

00:25:40.590 --> 00:25:43.810
you're completely done here.

00:25:43.810 --> 00:25:48.250
All right, so now we have
